{"key":"processedPost-12428004","value":{"id":12428004,"first":12421555,"last":16428088,"when":1271809545,"utime":"04/21/10 03:25 AM","content":"I'd disregard the difference between .8 and 1.2 inches of water column.&nbsp; <br /><br />If you've found a blower that will deliver 400 cfm @ .8\" it will work for an 18\" X 24\" filter.&nbsp; What you want is around 100 lineal feet per minute leaving the face of the flowhood.&nbsp; This means for a 1 square foot filter(12 X 12), you'd want a 100 cfm blower at .8\" to 1.2\" of static pressure in a perfect world.&nbsp; However, inside the plenum behind a flowhood is not a perfect world, so add about 20% to your calculations to account for friction, turns, blower efficiency, etc.","title":"Re: please help, brain hurts, hit with flowhood.","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}